oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: A Gold Medal
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Etching features a two-sided coin commemorating the Battle of New Orleans, Louisiana, 1815. Obverse shows General Andrew Jackson in profile and uniform. Reverse shows Lady Liberty instructing an angel to write a resolution commemorating the event. This item was in the Collection of Howard Memorial Library, New Orleans, La.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Wall, Bernhardt, 1872-1956
